1
00:00:09,833 --> 00:00:11,458
[NARRATOR]
Beasts known as The Nemesis

2
00:00:11,541 --> 00:00:13,625
wreak havoc on mankind.

3
00:00:13,708 --> 00:00:15,875
The only humans who can stand
against them

4
00:00:15,958 --> 00:00:17,625
are those called sorcerers.

5
00:00:17,708 --> 00:00:21,333
However, sorcerers are seen
as tainted by most

6
00:00:21,416 --> 00:00:24,250
and are regarded
with fear and distrust.

7
00:00:27,583 --> 00:00:30,583
[SETH] What?
How am I s'posed to afford that?

8
00:00:30,666 --> 00:00:32,666
No wonder it's covered
in dust, dude.

9
00:00:32,750 --> 00:00:34,833
Charging this much
is practically robbery.

10
00:00:34,916 --> 00:00:36,875
[SHOPKEEPER] Folding brooms are
legitimately expensive!

11
00:00:36,958 --> 00:00:38,875
You don't know anything,
so mind what you say!

12
00:00:38,958 --> 00:00:40,166
[SETH]
Huh?

13
00:00:40,250 --> 00:00:41,750
[ALMA]
That's odd.

14
00:00:41,833 --> 00:00:43,416
Thought you already
had a broom,

15
00:00:43,500 --> 00:00:44,833
and not the kind that folds.

16
00:00:44,916 --> 00:00:46,416
[SETH]
This one's for Melie.

17
00:00:46,500 --> 00:00:49,833
We lost everything we had on us
back in Rumble Town.

18
00:00:49,916 --> 00:00:51,250
[ALMA]
Mm-hmm...

19
00:00:53,458 --> 00:00:55,416
[ALMA]
So, about this Melie girl...

20
00:00:55,500 --> 00:00:57,375
I won't repeat
what her letter said,

21
00:00:57,458 --> 00:00:59,208
but you really did
give her a scare.

22
00:00:59,291 --> 00:01:01,208
-[SETH gasps]
-[ALMA sighs]

23
00:01:01,291 --> 00:01:03,250
Making a girl worry like that...

24
00:01:03,333 --> 00:01:05,666
thought I taught you better,
but it seems I was wrong.

25
00:01:05,750 --> 00:01:08,458
What? But why would anyone
be worried about me?

26
00:01:08,541 --> 00:01:11,500
I'm good enough at magic
to take care of myself now.

27
00:01:11,583 --> 00:01:14,083
[SETH grunting]

28
00:01:14,166 --> 00:01:15,833
Good grief.

29
00:01:15,916 --> 00:01:17,500
That's enough foolin' around.

30
00:01:17,583 --> 00:01:18,750
Let's go.

31
00:01:18,833 --> 00:01:19,958
Wait a second.

32
00:01:20,041 --> 00:01:21,541
Where are we going?

33
00:01:21,625 --> 00:01:23,750
You're supposed to take me
to see Yaga today, remember?

34
00:01:23,833 --> 00:01:25,000
Oh yeah, I forgot!

35
00:01:25,083 --> 00:01:26,583
You two go way back, right?

36
00:01:26,666 --> 00:01:28,166
What were you plannin'
to talk to him about?

37
00:01:29,500 --> 00:01:31,250
It has something to do
with Radiant.

38
00:01:31,333 --> 00:01:33,041
[gasps]

39
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:09,041
[NARRATOR]
"In Search of the Future"

40
00:03:12,041 --> 00:03:14,500
-[ALMA exhales]
-[SETH] Huh?

41
00:03:14,583 --> 00:03:16,916
[ALMA]
The heck is this?

42
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:18,625
[SETH]
Hmm...

43
00:03:18,708 --> 00:03:20,625
It says, "Please don't
look for me."

44
00:03:20,708 --> 00:03:22,250
[ALMA]
That senile coward.

45
00:03:22,333 --> 00:03:24,750
Can't believe he went this far
to avoid facing me!

46
00:03:24,833 --> 00:03:26,000
I'm confused.

47
00:03:26,083 --> 00:03:27,375
Isn't he an old friend of yours?

48
00:03:27,458 --> 00:03:28,791
I've known him a long time.

49
00:03:28,875 --> 00:03:31,791
He's been deathly scared of me
for most of it.

50
00:03:31,875 --> 00:03:33,416
-[SETH] Huh?
-Gimme the note.

51
00:03:33,500 --> 00:03:35,333
What else does it say?

52
00:03:35,416 --> 00:03:36,333
"Alma...

53
00:03:36,416 --> 00:03:38,166
"it has been quite a long time.

54
00:03:38,250 --> 00:03:40,500
"It's regrettable that, by
the time you read this letter,

55
00:03:40,583 --> 00:03:41,791
"I'll be far away.

56
00:03:41,875 --> 00:03:43,125
"Somewhere that you
could never find me,

57
00:03:43,208 --> 00:03:44,416
no matter how hard you--"

58
00:03:44,500 --> 00:03:46,666
Get to the point,
you old bastard!

59
00:03:46,750 --> 00:03:49,666
[YAGA] "Tell Seth to go
to Caislean Merlin.

60
00:03:49,750 --> 00:03:52,208
"I have it on good authority
that the Knight-sorcerers

61
00:03:52,291 --> 00:03:55,125
"who call it home
are searching for Radiant.

62
00:03:55,208 --> 00:03:57,541
They should be able to aid him
in his quest."

63
00:03:57,625 --> 00:03:59,416
Caislean Merlin, what's that?

64
00:03:59,500 --> 00:04:01,333
That'd be the capital
of Cyfandir.

65
00:04:01,416 --> 00:04:04,166
Which is a nation on
the neighboring continent.

66
00:04:04,250 --> 00:04:05,375
Ohh...

67
00:04:05,458 --> 00:04:07,375
[YAGA]
"He should be warned, though.

68
00:04:07,458 --> 00:04:09,541
"Perhaps as a result
of recent events,

69
00:04:09,625 --> 00:04:11,625
"the Inquisition
is planning to begin

70
00:04:11,708 --> 00:04:13,791
"a sorcerer-hunt
in Caislean Merlin.

71
00:04:13,875 --> 00:04:16,416
They're desperate, it seems."

72
00:04:16,500 --> 00:04:19,333
The Inquisition lost
a lot of influence.

73
00:04:19,416 --> 00:04:20,875
It's likely that they're just
doing this

74
00:04:20,958 --> 00:04:23,208
to try and salvage
their reputation.

75
00:04:23,291 --> 00:04:25,166
So, they're gonna make
scapegoats out of sorcerers

76
00:04:25,250 --> 00:04:27,291
who've done nothing wrong?

77
00:04:27,375 --> 00:04:29,791
Gah, no way
we can let that happen!

78
00:04:31,708 --> 00:04:32,916
[YAGA]
"Alma...

79
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:34,625
"In the short time
I've worked with him,

80
00:04:34,708 --> 00:04:37,958
"the apprentice you sent me
has developed a great deal.

81
00:04:38,041 --> 00:04:39,500
"We've reached a point

82
00:04:39,583 --> 00:04:41,708
"where what happens next
will depend on him.

83
00:04:41,791 --> 00:04:43,916
"He's as foolish as they come,
to be sure,

84
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:45,250
"but I have faith in the boy,

85
00:04:45,333 --> 00:04:47,208
"and I believe that
he'll find his answer,

86
00:04:47,291 --> 00:04:50,083
"long as he carves
his own path forward.

87
00:04:50,166 --> 00:04:52,125
"Which, in this old man's
opinion,

88
00:04:52,208 --> 00:04:55,625
is what it means to search
for Radiant in the first place."

89
00:04:55,708 --> 00:04:57,375
[ALMA]
Hmph.

90
00:04:57,458 --> 00:04:59,833
-Are you all right?
-[ALMA gasps]

91
00:04:59,916 --> 00:05:01,708
I was just thinkin'.

92
00:05:01,791 --> 00:05:03,166
What else did he write in there?

93
00:05:03,250 --> 00:05:05,166
Anything about where
he thinks Radiant might be?

94
00:05:05,250 --> 00:05:07,666
He says that you should carve
your own path forward.

95
00:05:07,750 --> 00:05:09,791
What the heck's
that s'posed to mean?

96
00:05:09,875 --> 00:05:11,333
It means that from here on out,

97
00:05:11,416 --> 00:05:14,166
you should start deciding
what's right for yourself.

98
00:05:14,250 --> 00:05:15,666
[SETH exhales]

99
00:05:18,041 --> 00:05:20,333
[DOC]
No way! Not happenin'!

100
00:05:20,416 --> 00:05:22,791
Why do you even wanna go
to Caislean Merlin?

101
00:05:22,875 --> 00:05:24,291
And what could've hit you
on the head

102
00:05:24,375 --> 00:05:26,125
so hard that you thought
I might wanna go with you?

103
00:05:26,208 --> 00:05:28,708
The Inquisition's planning to go
after all those sorcerers,

104
00:05:28,791 --> 00:05:30,708
so they're gonna need
all the help they can get!

105
00:05:30,791 --> 00:05:32,750
We can't just stand by
while it happens!

106
00:05:32,833 --> 00:05:34,083
There ain't a day of the week

107
00:05:34,166 --> 00:05:35,875
the Inquisitors aren't
goin' after someone!

108
00:05:35,958 --> 00:05:38,500
We can't always be chargin' off
to stop 'em.

109
00:05:38,583 --> 00:05:40,166
[huffs]
What's your problem?

110
00:05:40,250 --> 00:05:42,208
The three of us are supposed
to search for Radiant together,

111
00:05:42,291 --> 00:05:43,750
did you forget?

112
00:05:43,833 --> 00:05:45,500
[DOC] When did I agree to that?
Where's the contract?

113
00:05:45,583 --> 00:05:47,166
-Why would I sign it?!
-[PINK GUY hums]

114
00:05:47,250 --> 00:05:49,041
[DOC] I let you stick around me
for financial reasons only,

115
00:05:49,125 --> 00:05:50,208
and I'm reluctant about that!

116
00:05:50,291 --> 00:05:51,625
-[PINK GUY sighs]
-[SETH] Come on.

117
00:05:51,708 --> 00:05:53,750
If you really want me
to help you with this,

118
00:05:53,833 --> 00:05:54,958
then before you do anything,

119
00:05:55,041 --> 00:05:56,541
you gotta make enough
dough to pay off

120
00:05:56,625 --> 00:05:58,625
every cent
that I owe in your name.

121
00:05:58,708 --> 00:06:00,125
Once you've settled that,

122
00:06:00,208 --> 00:06:02,208
I might be willing to accept
your request as a job.

123
00:06:02,291 --> 00:06:03,541
[SETH groans]

124
00:06:03,625 --> 00:06:05,625
Look Doc,
I have to tell you,

125
00:06:05,708 --> 00:06:07,750
I don't have any problem
with helping him, personally--

126
00:06:07,833 --> 00:06:10,625
I understand that, Melie,
but at the end of the day,

127
00:06:10,708 --> 00:06:13,625
you need to remember that
you're here as my assistant.

128
00:06:13,708 --> 00:06:15,666
I get it, but I can't
just leave Seth

129
00:06:15,750 --> 00:06:17,291
to face danger
by himself, you know?

130
00:06:17,375 --> 00:06:20,000
It's not like he has to face
danger, he's lookin' for it!

131
00:06:20,083 --> 00:06:21,500
This numbskull tracked
down danger

132
00:06:21,583 --> 00:06:23,000
all the way
to another continent!

133
00:06:23,083 --> 00:06:24,416
-[SETH growls]
-I'm not going!

134
00:06:24,500 --> 00:06:25,666
There's no way you can
convince me

135
00:06:25,750 --> 00:06:27,500
to do somethin' scary like that!

136
00:06:27,583 --> 00:06:29,083
Oh my goodness.

137
00:06:29,166 --> 00:06:31,708
That doesn't sound like you,
Doc, what happened?

138
00:06:31,791 --> 00:06:33,458
Oh, nothin' to worry about.

139
00:06:33,541 --> 00:06:35,333
I was just explaining to young
Seth here

140
00:06:35,416 --> 00:06:38,000
that bein' careless
isn't the same as bein' brave!

141
00:06:38,083 --> 00:06:39,333
That's seems like good advice.

142
00:06:39,416 --> 00:06:41,250
You have such a mature outlook.

143
00:06:41,333 --> 00:06:43,541
[PAPA] Ha! Sounds to me
like he's bein' chicken.

144
00:06:43,625 --> 00:06:46,250
Makes sense,
he can't even use magic!

145
00:06:46,333 --> 00:06:47,333
-[DOC growls]
-[PAPA] What?

146
00:06:47,416 --> 00:06:48,750
Be nice, Papa.

147
00:06:48,833 --> 00:06:50,500
Doc's not a fighter,
he's a researcher.

148
00:06:50,583 --> 00:06:52,916
That's correct,
I am a man of science!

149
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:54,666
I've devoted my life
to investigating

150
00:06:54,750 --> 00:06:56,666
the many mysteries
of the world we live in.

151
00:06:56,750 --> 00:06:59,541
-You expect me to buy that?
-[DOC] Uhh...

152
00:06:59,625 --> 00:07:01,500
About my latest project, Melie.

153
00:07:01,583 --> 00:07:02,833
Yeah?

154
00:07:02,916 --> 00:07:04,458
[DOC] Could you run
a little errand for me?

155
00:07:04,541 --> 00:07:08,500
I need ya to pick some...
spotted mushrooms, for science.

156
00:07:08,583 --> 00:07:09,791
Well I don't mind,

157
00:07:09,875 --> 00:07:11,291
but do you need them
right this instant?

158
00:07:11,375 --> 00:07:12,916
[MISTER BOOBRIE chirps]

159
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:15,666
I've got an enormous debt
to start payin' off, by myself.

160
00:07:15,750 --> 00:07:19,250
So, I need to concoct somethin'
that'll rake in money and fast.

161
00:07:19,333 --> 00:07:21,291
I am so busy.

162
00:07:21,375 --> 00:07:23,875
-[SETH groans]
-Come on, Doc.

163
00:07:23,958 --> 00:07:25,875
Won't you at least
try to understand

164
00:07:25,958 --> 00:07:27,208
how Seth feels right now?

165
00:07:27,291 --> 00:07:30,208
Huh?! What about how I feel,
I almost died!

166
00:07:30,291 --> 00:07:33,250
I know, and I'm sure it was
really scary for you, but--

167
00:07:33,333 --> 00:07:36,458
It was! Have you ever been born
through your own stomach?!

168
00:07:36,541 --> 00:07:38,750
Stop lecturing me
and go do your job!

169
00:07:38,833 --> 00:07:41,583
Go on, you're not changin'
my mind about this.

170
00:07:41,666 --> 00:07:43,000
[MELIE]
Hmm...

171
00:07:43,083 --> 00:07:45,166
why do you have to be
so stubborn?!

172
00:07:45,250 --> 00:07:46,833
[MISTER BOOBRIE chirps]

173
00:07:46,916 --> 00:07:49,083
I think you upset her.

174
00:07:49,166 --> 00:07:51,041
[SETH sighs]

175
00:07:51,125 --> 00:07:52,541
What's your problem?

176
00:07:52,625 --> 00:07:55,416
You're supposed to be
our friend, so act like it.

177
00:07:55,500 --> 00:07:57,666
That's what I'm doin'.

178
00:07:57,750 --> 00:08:00,791
You were lucky to make it out
of Rumble Town alive.

179
00:08:00,875 --> 00:08:03,291
But even now, you're planning
to go pick fights

180
00:08:03,375 --> 00:08:04,916
with more
dangerous thaumaturges,

181
00:08:05,000 --> 00:08:07,625
-and psychopaths like Konrad.
-[SETH gasps]

182
00:08:07,708 --> 00:08:09,333
Think of Melie.

183
00:08:09,416 --> 00:08:12,125
Do you really wanna put her into
even more danger than you have?

184
00:08:12,208 --> 00:08:15,625
[SETH breathes shakily]
Hmm...

185
00:08:15,708 --> 00:08:18,583
♪

186
00:08:18,666 --> 00:08:20,958
[wind rushing]

187
00:08:26,916 --> 00:08:30,125
[SETH] Yeah... I was lucky
to make it out of there alive.

188
00:08:34,500 --> 00:08:36,625
If I really wanna find Radiant,

189
00:08:36,708 --> 00:08:40,125
it's possible that fights
like that will be unavoidable.

190
00:08:41,541 --> 00:08:44,875
The worst part's that I still
have no idea what Radiant is.

191
00:08:44,958 --> 00:08:48,791
The Nemesis aren't evil,
not in the slightest.

192
00:08:48,875 --> 00:08:51,750
So please, don't treat them
like monsters.

193
00:08:51,833 --> 00:08:53,833
[SETH]
I don't get it.

194
00:08:53,916 --> 00:08:56,541
If the Nemesis aren't evil,

195
00:08:56,625 --> 00:08:59,250
then what the heck are they?

196
00:09:03,708 --> 00:09:05,208
Hmm?

197
00:09:05,291 --> 00:09:08,833
Well... I guess that's even
more reason to keep going.

198
00:09:08,916 --> 00:09:10,833
If I wanna learn more
about the Nemesis,

199
00:09:10,916 --> 00:09:14,000
there's no better place
to start than Radiant!

200
00:09:14,083 --> 00:09:16,041
-[SETH chuckles]
-[MAJESTY] Ahh!

201
00:09:16,125 --> 00:09:19,208
It's the hero of
the Rumble Town riot!

202
00:09:19,291 --> 00:09:21,208
[SETH screams]

203
00:09:21,291 --> 00:09:23,541
[groans]

204
00:09:23,625 --> 00:09:25,083
[SETH]
Majesty!

205
00:09:25,166 --> 00:09:26,333
One King to another,

206
00:09:26,416 --> 00:09:27,583
you don't "appurr"

207
00:09:27,666 --> 00:09:29,250
to be "feline"
so good right meow.

208
00:09:29,333 --> 00:09:31,166
If you'd like to re-finance
some of your debt,

209
00:09:31,250 --> 00:09:32,583
I'm here for you.

210
00:09:32,666 --> 00:09:33,958
Fees may apply,

211
00:09:34,041 --> 00:09:35,500
-but your interest rates--
-[SETH] No.

212
00:09:35,583 --> 00:09:37,166
This has nothing to do
with my debt.

213
00:09:37,250 --> 00:09:39,000
[MAJESTY cackles]

214
00:09:39,083 --> 00:09:40,500
Then what's the matter?

215
00:09:40,583 --> 00:09:42,208
It isn't like you
to act this way.

216
00:09:42,291 --> 00:09:44,750
How exactly am I supposed
to be acting?

217
00:09:44,833 --> 00:09:46,791
If I had to describe
your "ar-cat-ype,"

218
00:09:46,875 --> 00:09:48,583
I suppose it would be
a snot-nosed kid

219
00:09:48,666 --> 00:09:50,041
-making weird noises
-[SETH growls]

220
00:09:50,125 --> 00:09:51,833
with a "purr-pawsterous" grin
on his face.

221
00:09:51,916 --> 00:09:53,833
What the heck
do you think I am?!

222
00:09:53,916 --> 00:09:55,375
[SETH]
Oh--

223
00:09:55,458 --> 00:09:57,958
Are you planning to leave
for Caislean Merlin soon?

224
00:09:58,041 --> 00:09:59,500
How did you know?

225
00:09:59,583 --> 00:10:02,041
I didn't become king of Artemis
through cuteness alone.

226
00:10:02,125 --> 00:10:05,291
And since you yourself are about
as sharp as a sack of wet mice,

227
00:10:05,375 --> 00:10:07,500
guessing what you plan
to do next was easy.

228
00:10:07,583 --> 00:10:08,958
[SETH]
Hmph...

229
00:10:09,041 --> 00:10:13,083
Hey, from what you know
of Caislean Merlin,

230
00:10:13,166 --> 00:10:14,833
does it seem dangerous?

231
00:10:14,916 --> 00:10:16,416
[MAJESTY]
Hmm...

232
00:10:16,500 --> 00:10:17,708
aside from Artemis,

233
00:10:17,791 --> 00:10:19,250
there is no place in this world

234
00:10:19,333 --> 00:10:22,166
that can claim to be
safe for sorcerers.

235
00:10:22,250 --> 00:10:23,875
[lightly gasps]

236
00:10:23,958 --> 00:10:26,000
Cyfandir is no exception.

237
00:10:26,083 --> 00:10:29,458
Wherever you go in your travels,
you'll be "purr-secuted."

238
00:10:29,541 --> 00:10:32,000
Why is that? Why do people
treat us sorcerers

239
00:10:32,083 --> 00:10:33,916
like we're barely even human?

240
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:35,375
You've seen
the reason "fur" that

241
00:10:35,458 --> 00:10:36,458
with your own eyes.

242
00:10:36,541 --> 00:10:38,041
Human beings are pre-disposed

243
00:10:38,125 --> 00:10:42,000
to hate and fear
those who are unlike them.

244
00:10:42,083 --> 00:10:44,708
Oh, speaking of mistreating
your fellow man.

245
00:10:44,791 --> 00:10:46,083
I went ahead and added

246
00:10:46,166 --> 00:10:48,000
the "clawst" of our recent party
to your debt.

247
00:10:48,083 --> 00:10:49,416
What?
You're kidding!

248
00:10:49,500 --> 00:10:51,583
If anything, my debt
should've been lowered!

249
00:10:51,666 --> 00:10:52,958
[MAJESTY]
Don't forget that I arranged

250
00:10:53,041 --> 00:10:54,666
for a train to bring you home.

251
00:10:54,750 --> 00:10:56,125
Even if we put that aside,

252
00:10:56,208 --> 00:10:58,500
the entailed cost of your use
of our facilities

253
00:10:58,583 --> 00:11:01,083
still outweighs
any reward you earned.

254
00:11:01,166 --> 00:11:03,916
[ALMA] Still the same greedy
fat-cat I remember.

255
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:05,625
-Eh, Majesty?
-[SETH lightly gasps]

256
00:11:05,708 --> 00:11:07,291
Oh-- Alma!

257
00:11:07,375 --> 00:11:09,208
[cackles]

258
00:11:09,291 --> 00:11:10,416
Hello there!

259
00:11:10,500 --> 00:11:12,416
About time you decided
to visit home.

260
00:11:12,500 --> 00:11:15,458
You know full well that
this place isn't my home.

261
00:11:15,541 --> 00:11:18,125
Artemis is a home
for every sorcerer alive,

262
00:11:18,208 --> 00:11:19,791
whether they
contribute or not.

263
00:11:19,875 --> 00:11:21,166
You might've liked it here,

264
00:11:21,250 --> 00:11:22,916
if you'd "pawsed"
before judging.

265
00:11:23,000 --> 00:11:26,416
Ugh... I'm only here at
the moment because of my work.

266
00:11:26,500 --> 00:11:28,000
[MAJESTY]
Tell me "somefang,"

267
00:11:28,083 --> 00:11:29,833
is this the child
you spoke of?

268
00:11:29,916 --> 00:11:31,750
The one you raised yourself?

269
00:11:31,833 --> 00:11:33,291
That he is.

270
00:11:33,375 --> 00:11:36,291
-[SETH] Huh?
-[MAJESTY cackles]

271
00:11:36,375 --> 00:11:39,333
Be sure that you come back here
to settle your "tabby."

272
00:11:39,416 --> 00:11:41,083
All right, King of Debt?

273
00:11:41,166 --> 00:11:43,041
[lightly gasps]

274
00:11:43,125 --> 00:11:46,333
You don't actually think he'd
run off without paying, do you?

275
00:11:46,416 --> 00:11:47,833
Of course I don't.

276
00:11:47,916 --> 00:11:50,791
It won't even cross
the snot-nosed imbecile's mind.

277
00:11:50,875 --> 00:11:52,125
True...

278
00:11:52,208 --> 00:11:54,541
My point is I can't have you
dying out there.

279
00:11:54,625 --> 00:11:57,041
Scratch that-- even if you die,
I still want my money.

280
00:11:57,125 --> 00:11:58,375
That's harsh!

281
00:11:58,458 --> 00:12:00,708
And by the way,
my nose isn't snotty at all!

282
00:12:00,791 --> 00:12:02,083
[MAJESTY cackles]

283
00:12:02,166 --> 00:12:05,541
[SETH straining, stammering
in anger]

284
00:12:05,625 --> 00:12:08,416
[GRIMM]
Caislean Merlin, eh?

285
00:12:08,500 --> 00:12:09,958
Given the nature of his quest,

286
00:12:10,041 --> 00:12:13,125
he's bound to run into
the Knight-Sorcerers there.

287
00:12:13,208 --> 00:12:14,750
In that case...

288
00:12:14,833 --> 00:12:16,333
-[siren blaring]
-[GRIMM] Hmm?

289
00:12:16,416 --> 00:12:18,875
-[BOTH] Hmm?
-What's going on?

290
00:12:18,958 --> 00:12:21,250
[siren continues]

291
00:12:25,416 --> 00:12:27,291
Those look like Nemesis eggs.

292
00:12:27,375 --> 00:12:29,208
-How are there so many?
-[MAJESTY] Hmm...

293
00:12:29,291 --> 00:12:30,916
It would appear that Artemis
has entered

294
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:33,458
a fairly dangerous
part of the sky.

295
00:12:33,541 --> 00:12:35,583
Thought this city
was supposed to be safe.

296
00:12:35,666 --> 00:12:36,958
[MAJESTY cackles]

297
00:12:37,041 --> 00:12:39,375
[MAJESTY]
Deploy the defensive barrier!

298
00:12:39,458 --> 00:12:40,958
[energy charging]

299
00:12:42,041 --> 00:12:44,375
Mobilize our forces!

300
00:12:44,458 --> 00:12:46,416
Intercept the foe!

301
00:12:49,083 --> 00:12:50,500
[SETH]
Hmph...

302
00:12:58,041 --> 00:12:59,166
Tone it down, people!

303
00:12:59,250 --> 00:13:01,000
What's with all the ruckus
out here?!

304
00:13:01,083 --> 00:13:02,458
-Oh, dear...
-Got a business to run.

305
00:13:02,541 --> 00:13:04,958
Nemesis eggs,
and so many.

306
00:13:05,041 --> 00:13:07,500
Hope they don't break
through the barrier.

307
00:13:07,583 --> 00:13:09,166
Think they can handle this?

308
00:13:09,250 --> 00:13:10,458
Yeah.

309
00:13:10,541 --> 00:13:13,000
The Artemis Institute
is well protected.

310
00:13:13,083 --> 00:13:14,291
If you're sure...

311
00:13:14,375 --> 00:13:15,458
-[ALMA] Seth.
-[SETH] Hmm?

312
00:13:15,541 --> 00:13:17,541
I'm heading back
to my ship for now.

313
00:13:17,625 --> 00:13:19,625
Try not to do anything stupid
while I'm gone.

314
00:13:19,708 --> 00:13:22,000
Uh-- right.

315
00:13:22,083 --> 00:13:26,041
[explosions]

316
00:13:29,000 --> 00:13:30,916
[sighs]

317
00:13:31,000 --> 00:13:32,583
[NICK]
What's the matter, Seth?

318
00:13:32,666 --> 00:13:34,500
You look a bit uneasy.

319
00:13:34,583 --> 00:13:36,458
[SETH excitedly]
Nick, hey.

320
00:13:36,541 --> 00:13:38,875
Care to explain why
you're just standing there?

321
00:13:38,958 --> 00:13:41,833
Wait, I don't suppose it's
because you're frozen in terror?

322
00:13:41,916 --> 00:13:43,375
But if that's the case,

323
00:13:43,458 --> 00:13:45,375
then all those stories
of your exploits in Rumble Town

324
00:13:45,458 --> 00:13:46,666
must've been made up.

325
00:13:46,750 --> 00:13:48,291
Right?

326
00:13:48,375 --> 00:13:50,041
[BOTH HENCHMEN] Nice one,
Nick, you could be a detective!

327
00:13:50,125 --> 00:13:52,041
Well, I, for one,
already knew you were

328
00:13:52,125 --> 00:13:53,791
a cowardly little charlatan.

329
00:13:53,875 --> 00:13:55,666
I'll take care of the scary
Nemeses,

330
00:13:55,750 --> 00:13:57,291
you just watch and learn.

331
00:13:57,375 --> 00:13:58,916
Wait, don't attack them!

332
00:13:59,000 --> 00:14:01,291
I found out from Hameline
that not all Nemeses are bad!

333
00:14:01,375 --> 00:14:03,875
Huh?
The hell you trying to say?!

334
00:14:03,958 --> 00:14:05,916
Bringing an end to the scourge
of the Nemesis

335
00:14:06,000 --> 00:14:08,750
is what any sorcerer who's
worth their salt lives for!

336
00:14:08,833 --> 00:14:10,666
[HENCHMAN A]
Yeah, Nick, that's the spirit!

337
00:14:10,750 --> 00:14:12,750
[HENCHMAN B] Wow!
That's one heck of a reason

338
00:14:12,833 --> 00:14:14,041
to live, Nick!

339
00:14:14,125 --> 00:14:15,083
-[whooshing]
-[SETH gasps]

340
00:14:16,083 --> 00:14:16,958
[gasps]

341
00:14:17,958 --> 00:14:19,333
-[loud boom]
-[NICK] Gah!

342
00:14:19,416 --> 00:14:21,583
Looks like one of them
slipped past our defenses!

343
00:14:21,666 --> 00:14:23,500
I'd have stopped it,
but you distracted me.

344
00:14:23,583 --> 00:14:25,250
[SETH huffs]

345
00:14:25,333 --> 00:14:27,458
-[DOC] Hey!
-[SETH] Huh?

346
00:14:27,541 --> 00:14:29,166
[panting]
Seth!

347
00:14:29,250 --> 00:14:30,500
[SETH]
What's wrong?!

348
00:14:30,583 --> 00:14:32,166
It's about Melie!

349
00:14:32,250 --> 00:14:34,416
She went off to pick mushrooms
on an island over that way.

350
00:14:34,500 --> 00:14:35,708
You mean she's not here?

351
00:14:35,791 --> 00:14:37,250
-[nervously exhales]
-[DOC] That's right.

352
00:14:37,333 --> 00:14:39,833
And she might not even know
what's going on.

353
00:14:39,916 --> 00:14:41,541
[NICK scoffs]

354
00:14:41,625 --> 00:14:44,041
Sounds like your friend's gotten
herself into quite the pickle.

355
00:14:44,125 --> 00:14:45,333
[SETH] I'm sorry about this,

356
00:14:45,416 --> 00:14:46,958
but Imma need to borrow
your broom, Nick!

357
00:14:47,041 --> 00:14:48,333
[NICK screams]

358
00:14:48,416 --> 00:14:50,833
-[NICK groans]
-[NICK'S HENCHMEN] Nick!

359
00:14:50,916 --> 00:14:53,250
[SETH]
Thanks! I'll return this later,

360
00:14:53,333 --> 00:14:54,333
-I promise!
-[broom whooshing]

361
00:14:54,416 --> 00:14:56,333
[NICK yelps]
Hey!

362
00:14:56,416 --> 00:14:59,791
Get back here.

363
00:15:06,333 --> 00:15:08,750
Doc is really being a jerk.

364
00:15:08,833 --> 00:15:10,416
If he needs these mushrooms
so badly,

365
00:15:10,500 --> 00:15:12,125
he should be
picking them with me.

366
00:15:12,208 --> 00:15:14,250
[MISTER BOOBRIE chirps
in agreement]

367
00:15:14,333 --> 00:15:15,291
[MISTER BOOBRIE]
Huh?

368
00:15:15,375 --> 00:15:16,333
[whooshing]

369
00:15:16,416 --> 00:15:17,791
-[crash]
-[MELIE screams]

370
00:15:17,875 --> 00:15:21,333
-[BOTH whimpering]
-[MELIE] Huh?

371
00:15:22,541 --> 00:15:24,250
[MELIE]
Wait...

372
00:15:24,333 --> 00:15:26,791
that looks like a Nemesis egg!

373
00:15:26,875 --> 00:15:29,041
[crackling]

374
00:15:30,375 --> 00:15:32,250
-[explosion]
-[NEMESIS roars]

375
00:15:32,333 --> 00:15:34,041
[NEMESIS snarls]

376
00:15:36,083 --> 00:15:37,041
[BOTH gasp]

377
00:15:37,125 --> 00:15:39,083
[screaming]

378
00:15:41,083 --> 00:15:44,000
-[MISTER BOOBRIE chirps]
-Thanks, Mister Boobrie!

379
00:15:44,083 --> 00:15:46,625
Try to hang in there!

380
00:15:49,875 --> 00:15:50,958
Huh?

381
00:15:51,958 --> 00:15:53,583
[screams]

382
00:15:53,666 --> 00:15:55,291
[NEMESIS roars]

383
00:15:55,375 --> 00:15:56,333
[whimpering]

384
00:15:56,416 --> 00:15:58,333
[SETH]
Phew! Melie, Boobrie.

385
00:15:58,416 --> 00:15:59,583
You all right?

386
00:15:59,666 --> 00:16:01,125
You found us.

387
00:16:01,208 --> 00:16:03,541
-[MISTER BOOBRIE chirps]
-[BOTH gasp]

388
00:16:03,625 --> 00:16:05,541
[NEMESIS growls]

389
00:16:05,625 --> 00:16:08,583
That looks like
a strong one.

390
00:16:08,666 --> 00:16:11,000
Make sure to hang on tight,
okay?

391
00:16:11,083 --> 00:16:12,708
Right!

392
00:16:12,791 --> 00:16:15,125
[NEMESIS roars]

393
00:16:17,750 --> 00:16:19,458
[NEMESIS growls]

394
00:16:21,208 --> 00:16:22,458
[explosion]

395
00:16:23,750 --> 00:16:25,375
[NEMESIS roars]

396
00:16:26,583 --> 00:16:27,750
I just can't shake it.

397
00:16:27,833 --> 00:16:29,291
I have an idea.

398
00:16:29,375 --> 00:16:32,125
[NEMESIS roars]

399
00:16:33,666 --> 00:16:34,583
[NEMESIS growls]

400
00:16:34,666 --> 00:16:36,416
[SETH grunts]

401
00:16:38,500 --> 00:16:41,541
[MELIE]
Gravem Carserem!

402
00:16:41,625 --> 00:16:42,500
[NEMESIS squawks]

403
00:16:44,583 --> 00:16:46,208
[MELIE]
Here's your chance, Seth!

404
00:16:46,291 --> 00:16:47,541
[MISTER BOOBRIE chirps]

405
00:16:47,625 --> 00:16:48,583
[SETH]
Right!

406
00:16:48,666 --> 00:16:52,541
Skull... Attack!

407
00:16:52,625 --> 00:16:54,541
[explosion]

408
00:16:57,625 --> 00:16:59,125
[NEMESIS groans]

409
00:17:04,125 --> 00:17:05,750
We actually beat it!

410
00:17:05,833 --> 00:17:07,166
[MISTER BOOBRIE chirps]

411
00:17:09,208 --> 00:17:11,416
-[water sloshing]
-[SETH sighs]

412
00:17:12,666 --> 00:17:14,333
[SETH]
Please be calm.

413
00:17:14,416 --> 00:17:16,500
Don't force us to kill you.

414
00:17:16,583 --> 00:17:18,375
-[MELIE] Seth...
-[SETH gasps]

415
00:17:18,458 --> 00:17:20,166
Thank you so much for coming!

416
00:17:20,250 --> 00:17:22,625
If it wasn't for you,
we'd be in that thing's belly.

417
00:17:22,708 --> 00:17:24,500
You were
seriously amazing, Seth,

418
00:17:24,583 --> 00:17:26,416
-I don't know how to thank you!
-[SETH gasps]

419
00:17:27,958 --> 00:17:29,083
-[NEMESIS bleats]
-[SETH] Melie!

420
00:17:29,166 --> 00:17:30,125
[MELIE]
Huh?!

421
00:17:30,208 --> 00:17:31,625
[SETH grunts]

422
00:17:31,708 --> 00:17:33,625
-[MISTER BOOBRIE chirps]
-Oh, no!

423
00:17:33,708 --> 00:17:35,625
[SETH straining]

424
00:17:35,708 --> 00:17:37,166
♪

425
00:17:42,833 --> 00:17:44,333
[muffled scream]

426
00:17:44,416 --> 00:17:46,416
Let him go!

427
00:17:49,291 --> 00:17:50,458
[SETH growls]

428
00:17:51,625 --> 00:17:53,416
[explosion]

429
00:17:53,500 --> 00:17:55,916
[BOTH scream]

430
00:17:57,708 --> 00:18:00,666
[SETH roaring]

431
00:18:00,750 --> 00:18:02,125
[ALMA grunts]

432
00:18:02,208 --> 00:18:04,791
This isn't one of
my usual headaches.

433
00:18:04,875 --> 00:18:06,166
What's wrong, Seth?

434
00:18:06,250 --> 00:18:09,666
[BOTH roaring]

435
00:18:09,750 --> 00:18:11,333
[boom]

436
00:18:12,833 --> 00:18:16,500
[explosion]

437
00:18:16,583 --> 00:18:19,583
-Whoa, Seth...
-[MISTER BOOBRIE chirps]

438
00:18:23,416 --> 00:18:25,458
[sighs]

439
00:18:25,541 --> 00:18:28,000
[exhales]
Huh?

440
00:18:28,083 --> 00:18:30,583
[breathes shakily]

441
00:18:33,125 --> 00:18:35,333
What did I do?

442
00:18:35,416 --> 00:18:37,375
Not again.

443
00:18:41,375 --> 00:18:44,291
[BOTH whimper]

444
00:18:44,375 --> 00:18:46,166
♪

445
00:18:51,333 --> 00:18:54,500
[GRIMM] That boy's power is
in equal parts unnatural...

446
00:18:54,583 --> 00:18:55,875
and dangerous.

447
00:18:55,958 --> 00:18:58,625
This mystery warrants
further investigation.

448
00:18:58,708 --> 00:19:00,208
Grimm will have to see more.

449
00:19:00,291 --> 00:19:03,416
♪

450
00:19:17,916 --> 00:19:19,791
[sighs]

451
00:19:23,958 --> 00:19:25,750
[sighs]

452
00:19:25,833 --> 00:19:27,750
Hmph.

453
00:19:27,833 --> 00:19:30,125
[SHOPKEEPER humming]

454
00:19:30,208 --> 00:19:33,708
[SHOPKEEPER] Oh, another day
of hard work comes to a close.

455
00:19:33,791 --> 00:19:35,333
Oh, how I've been
looking forward

456
00:19:35,416 --> 00:19:37,041
to an evening
of peace and quiet.

457
00:19:37,125 --> 00:19:38,583
-[chuckles]
-[SETH] Please, wait!

458
00:19:38,666 --> 00:19:39,750
[SHOPKEEPER exclaims]

459
00:19:39,833 --> 00:19:42,375
I wanna get that
broom after all.

460
00:19:44,333 --> 00:19:48,291
[birds chirping]

461
00:19:52,291 --> 00:19:54,166
[sighs]

462
00:19:54,250 --> 00:19:56,333
Hmph.

463
00:19:58,125 --> 00:19:59,250
Morning Seth!

464
00:19:59,333 --> 00:20:01,041
Do ya wanna come
get some coffee? Uh--

465
00:20:01,125 --> 00:20:02,833
Huh...?

466
00:20:06,000 --> 00:20:08,041
His stuff's gone.

467
00:20:08,125 --> 00:20:09,791
[whimpers]

468
00:20:09,875 --> 00:20:11,666
[sighs]

469
00:20:13,541 --> 00:20:14,791
[lightly gasps]

470
00:20:14,875 --> 00:20:16,791
[SETH] "Before I say
anything else,

471
00:20:16,875 --> 00:20:18,291
"thanks for everything.

472
00:20:18,375 --> 00:20:20,291
"I guess I'm just starting
to realize

473
00:20:20,375 --> 00:20:22,458
"how dangerous
this journey'll be.

474
00:20:22,541 --> 00:20:24,875
"And I don't wanna cause you
any more trouble.

475
00:20:24,958 --> 00:20:26,958
So, I'm leaving."
-[whimpers]

476
00:20:27,041 --> 00:20:29,375
[SETH] "The broom on the table
is a parting gift.

477
00:20:29,458 --> 00:20:31,333
I hope you like it."

478
00:20:33,291 --> 00:20:35,208
[MELIE crying]
Why?

479
00:20:41,791 --> 00:20:44,375
[ALMA] Starting to wish you'd
told them goodbye?

480
00:20:45,541 --> 00:20:47,041
[SETH]
Hmph...

481
00:20:47,125 --> 00:20:49,833
if I had, then I would've
wanted to stay with them.

482
00:20:49,916 --> 00:20:51,375
And I can't.

483
00:20:51,458 --> 00:20:52,708
Least not as I am.

484
00:20:52,791 --> 00:20:55,208
Until I learn to control
this power,

485
00:20:55,291 --> 00:20:58,000
I'm just as likely to hurt
my friends as to help them.

486
00:20:58,083 --> 00:20:59,583
So, there's no other choice.

487
00:20:59,666 --> 00:21:02,583
Fair enough.

488
00:21:02,666 --> 00:21:04,083
You've made your decision,

489
00:21:04,166 --> 00:21:05,958
it doesn't matter to me.

490
00:21:06,041 --> 00:21:07,708
[SETH sighs]

491
00:21:11,125 --> 00:21:12,666
Seth took off.

492
00:21:12,750 --> 00:21:15,333
And he didn't even bother
tellin' us goodbye.

493
00:21:15,416 --> 00:21:17,250
-That's awful.
-[PAPA groans]

494
00:21:17,333 --> 00:21:20,666
The boy had a lot on his mind,
and that includes all of you.

495
00:21:20,750 --> 00:21:21,833
He didn't wish to cause you

496
00:21:21,916 --> 00:21:23,041
-any further trouble.
-[DOC] Huh?

497
00:21:23,125 --> 00:21:24,416
That's my guess.

498
00:21:24,500 --> 00:21:26,583
Yeah, the kid could be
a nuisance sometimes,

499
00:21:26,666 --> 00:21:28,500
but I didn't want him to just--

500
00:21:28,583 --> 00:21:29,875
No, come to think of it,

501
00:21:29,958 --> 00:21:32,250
I'm better off havin'
